name: OpenALPR 2.3.0
body:
- Option for plate detection mask and prewarp config changes via API
- Python3 support
- Improved plate pattern correctness
- Bug fixes
- Accuracy improvements

name: OpenALPR 2.2.0
body:
- Added training data for Singapore and Great Britain
- Improved accuracy and reduced false positives for US plate detector
- Improved support for 2-line plates (requires training data)
- Supports analyzing multiple training datasets in one pass
- Added OpenCL GPU support (works with Nvidia, AMD, and Intel GPUs)
- Upgraded to OpenCV 3.0
- Support Tesseract 3.04
- .NET library API improvements
- Bug Fixes

name: OpenALPR 2.1.0
body:
- Added per-character details to API output
- Bug fixes
- Added camera calibration utility
- Motion detector for video frames
- Full UTF-8 character support
- Support for South Korean and Australian plates
- Experimental morphological plate detector
- Pattern matching for European countries

name: OpenALPR 2.0.1
body:
- Bindings for Java, C#, and Python
- API changes/simplification
- CUDA support
- Bug fixes
- Faster initial load time
- Additional Config options
- Library supports multi-line plates

name: OpenALPR 1.2.0
body:
## Major new features
- Linux Daemon
- Upgraded to Tesseract 3.03
- Improved performance and accuracy
- MJPEG video support

## Minor new features
- Simplified build process for Windows
- End-to-end accuracy benchmarks added
- Bug fixes

name: OpenALPR 1.1.0
body:
Bug Fixes
Better timing on Windows
Multithreaded plate detection
Performance improvements
Simpler build for Windows
Improved plate edge detection
Support multiple redirecting plate file names from standard in

name: OpenALPR v1.0.0
body: This is the first official release of OpenALPR.  Windows and Linux binaries are attached.
